    "body": "Sorry,  but this doesn't seem quite right.  You've defined the parameter `data` as bytes32, and then you've got `keccak256(data)` on line 1 of the implementation.  That causes a compiler errror (wants `bytes`, not `bytes32` as aparemeter to `keccak256`), ( Because data is bytes32 I thought you were proposing that one should sign a hash of the message, rather than the message itself).   Should the 'data' parameter actually be bytes not bytes32? And if you do sign a hash of the message rather than the message itself how should a hash32 between turned into a bytes for the purposes of this this method?   ",
